      "message": "I didn\u0027t understand your comment.\n\nIt follows same rules as all other calls:\n1. If caller has no READER role for the prefix, returns PERMISSION_DENIED.\n2. If caller has READER role for the prefix, but not OWNER, and package exists, returns PERMISSION_DENIED.\n3. If caller has READER role for the prefix or above, and packages does NOT exist, returns NOT_FOUND.\n\nSpelling this out in every RPC call is kind of frustrating, so I\u0027m omitting it to most common case of \"no access \u003d\u003e PERMISSION_DENIED\".",
